  "id": "enhanced_vegetation_index",
  "summary": "Visualizes Enhanced Vegetation Index 2 (EVI2) from Sentinel-2 imagery using a fixed color-ramp palette to highlight vegetation signal strength while reducing sensitivity to soil background and atmospheric effects.",
  "description": "Calculates the Enhanced Vegetation Index 2 (EVI2) from Sentinel-2 L2A imagery. EVI2 is a two-band vegetation index derived from near-infrared (B08) and red (B04) reflectance, designed to strengthen the vegetation signal in dense canopies while reducing sensitivity to soil background and atmospheric influences. Results are rendered using a fixed threshold-to-RGB color ramp for intuitive interpretation from low to high vegetation signal."
